A wide beach scene at golden hour in Studio Ghibli style, showing an elaborate sand castle city sprawling across wet sand near the water's edge. Small figures of children and adults are scattered around, some kneeling with buckets and tools, others carrying water from the gentle waves. The sand structures include sweeping walls reminiscent of ancient fortifications, curved amphitheater shapes, and delicate towers with arched bridges connecting them. Soft watercolor-like clouds drift in a warm peachy-orange sky, and the incoming tide creates mirror-like reflections. Scattered wooden sand-shaping tools and colorful plastic buckets dot the scene. The atmosphere conveys focused joy and collaborative creation, with each builder absorbed in their own corner of this temporary kingdom rising from ordinary beach sand.
